Issues.Body:
### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

common

### Is this a regression?

Yes

### Description

if set a properties of class with the value of acces on trackby, trackby can't acces of him properties. For example, this: 

```
sameDaddy(index, item) {
    console.log(this.elementCompareToogle);
    if (this.orderReturnValue) {
      return item.value[this.elementCompareToogle];//dentro de la funcion no carga el elementCompareTrackBy 
    } else {
      return item.value['pos1'];
    }
  }
```
I think that the function send for reference and have different scope than this.elementCompareToogle. Because if i called the funcion on template with interpolation the function grab well the value of properties,  The same pass with the child trackby.
Class of use: 
```
import { BaseTableComponent } from './../base-table/base-table.component';
import { Component, OnInit, Output, EventEmitter } from '@angular/core';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-table-map',
  templateUrl: './table-map.component.html',
  styleUrls: ['./table-map.component.css']
})
export class TableMapComponent extends BaseTableComponent implements OnInit {
  @Output() onClickButton = new EventEmitter();
  constructor() {
    super();

  }

  ngOnInit(): void {
  }
  handlerAccion(data) {
    this.onClickButton.emit(data);
  }
  sameDaddy(index, item) {
    console.log(this.elementCompareToogle);
    if (this.orderReturnValue) {
      return item.value[this.elementCompareToogle];//dentro de la funcion no carga el elementCompareTrackBy 
    } else {
      return item.value['pos1'];
    }
  }
  sameChild(index, item) {
    super.sameChild(index, item);
  }
}
```

The html:
`<div *ngIf="mostrarError==0">
    <ftcomun-alert-message [msg]="tittleError" [type]="'error'"></ftcomun-alert-message>
</div>
